<cell id="cell-0"><cell_type>markdown</cell_type># MedAlign — Build Hybrid RAG Index (Kaggle GPU)
Embeds PubMedQA passages with BGE-large on GPU (~10–20 min vs hours on CPU laptop).
Outputs FAISS + BM25 + metadata → HuggingFace Hub dataset → laptop pulls them locally.</cell id="cell-0">
<cell id="cell-1">!pip -q install -U sentence-transformers faiss-cpu rank-bm25 datasets huggingface_hub pyyaml
!pip -q install git+https://github.com/zubairashfaque/medalign-rlhf.git</cell id="cell-1">
<cell id="cell-2">from kaggle_secrets import UserSecretsClient
import os
u = UserSecretsClient()
os.environ['HF_TOKEN'] = u.get_secret('HF_TOKEN')
from huggingface_hub import login
login(os.environ['HF_TOKEN'])</cell id="cell-2">
<cell id="cell-3"># Pull the RAG config + script from the repo
!mkdir -p configs scripts
!wget -q https://raw.githubusercontent.com/zubairashfaque/medalign-rlhf/main/configs/rag.yaml -O configs/rag.yaml
!wget -q https://raw.githubusercontent.com/zubairashfaque/medalign-rlhf/main/scripts/build_rag_index.py -O scripts/build_rag_index.py
!cat configs/rag.yaml</cell id="cell-3">
<cell id="cell-4"># Verify GPU available (T4 has ~16 GB — BGE-large fits comfortably)
import torch
print('CUDA:', torch.cuda.is_available(), '| Device:', torch.cuda.get_device_name(0) if torch.cuda.is_available() else 'CPU')</cell id="cell-4">
<cell id="cell-5"># Run the index build. SentenceTransformer auto-uses CUDA when available.
!python scripts/build_rag_index.py</cell id="cell-5">
<cell id="cell-6">!ls -lh data/rag/</cell id="cell-6">
<cell id="cell-7"># Push the 3 artifacts to HF Hub as a dataset so the laptop can pull them
from huggingface_hub import HfApi, create_repo
REPO_ID = 'Zubairash/medalign-rag-index'
create_repo(REPO_ID, repo_type='dataset', exist_ok=True)
api = HfApi()
api.upload_folder(
    folder_path='data/rag',
    repo_id=REPO_ID,
    repo_type='dataset',
    commit_message='RAG index built on Kaggle (BGE-large on T4)',
)
print(f'Done. Pull on laptop:\n  huggingface-cli download {REPO_ID} --repo-type dataset --local-dir data/rag')</cell id="cell-7">